title: wukong_(league_of_legends)
body:
A [[vastaya|vastayan]] monkey Champion from the Plague Jungles in [[League of Legends]]. He is usually played solo top or mid. Best known for his jerky yet laid-back style and ability to confuse enemies with a decoy. His weapon is modeled after the 'Monkey King Bar', a staff that, despite weighing several tons, can grow or shrink at will.

Trained in the art of Wuju Style by its primary practitioner [[master yi|Master Yi]].

Inspired by [[Sun Wukong]] from [[journey to the west|Journey to the West]].

Full title: [b]Wukong the Monkey King[/b]

Lulu has [[green eyes]], a [[long_hair|long]] [[purple_hair|purple]] hair and [[animal ears]]. She wears a [[witch hat]] and carries a [[staff]] around with her.

She is known for her whimsical nature and ability to polymorph or shrink/enlarge others. Has a [[fairy|faerie]] companion named [[Pix (league of legends)|]].

Full title: [b]Lulu, the Fae Sorceress[/b]

title: sei_shounagon_(fate)
body:
An archer-class servant introduced in [[Fate/Grand Order]].

An author, poet and court lady to Empress Fujiwara no Teishi. Shounagon authored "The Pillow Book":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Pillow_Book, a book of observations and personal musings she had during her service to the Empress. She is designed by [[mika_pikazo|Mika Pikazo]].

Intially called herself as Kirakira no Archer, "The Sparkling Archer". She later refers to herself with her informal name Nagiko. She is a contemporary and rival of [[Murasaki Shikibu_(Fate)|]].

A notable [[otaku]] who tried to be as youthful and "in-touch" with modern culture as possible. Which were shown by her Noble Phantasm [[Emotional Engine - Full Drive]], which features a [[double v]], as well as her (in)famous [[dab_(dance)|dabbing]] attack pose.

title: road_bicycle
body:
The term road bicycle is used to describe bicycles built for traveling at speed on paved roads. Some sources use the term to mean racing bicycle.

Compared to other styles of bicycle, road bicycles share common features:

* The tires are narrow, high-pressure (100 psi (700 kPa) or higher), and smooth to decrease rolling resistance
* The handlebars are bent ("dropped") to allow the rider position to be leaned forward and downward, which reduces the forward vertical cross sectional area and thus highly reduces the air resistance
* They usually use derailleur gears; however, single-speed and fixed-gear varieties exist
* They either use disc brakes or rim brakes (although there might be technical differences, for example road bike calliper brakes use shorter and wider pads than mountain bike cantilevers)
* The bicycle is of a lightweight construction

title: mountain_bicycle
body: A mountain bike (MTB) or mountain bicycle is a bicycle designed for off-road cycling. Mountain bikes share some similarities with other bicycles but incorporate features designed to enhance durability and performance in rough terrain, which makes them heavier, more complex, and less efficient on smooth surfaces.

title: cruiser_bicycle

title: eggette
body:
A [i][[Sonic (series)|]][/i] [[original]] fan character based off of [[Dr. Eggman]] as he appears in [i][[Sonic Mania]][/i]. Also sometimes called Omelette or Eggatha.

In Flying Battery Zone Act 2, Eggman fights the player in a spider [[mecha]] internally referred to as the "Spider Mobile". The original sprite she derived from simply had Eggman hanging upside down in the mecha. The trend only really began to take off due to "an interpretation":https://twitter.com/blackbookalpha/status/901971073096335360 by [[Alpha Gamboa]]; due to the fact that his visible face looked like that of a young girl in that state, the user had drawn the "head" of that sprite as a young girl with Eggman's trademarked glasses and a tiara reinterpreted from Eggman's nose, and her costume directly inspired from the Spider Mobile's design. From that point on, fans began to draw the character closely resembling that original version.

In most versions she's portrayed as an entity akin to [[Bowser Jr.]]: a bratty younger version of her "parent". However, whether she's actually related to Eggman or not is usually up for interpretation; in some she's blood by cloning, by her being a niece, or some coupling, and in others she's an [[android]] powered by a jewel on her head. In any case, she is just as technologically proficient as her originator and antagonizes [[Sonic the Hedgehog]] as well.

Do not mistake her for a younger genderswap of Dr. Eggman (see [[Eggmaam]] for a genderswap instead), nor a transformation in the vein of [[Super Crown]] fan characters (which often use the "-ette" suffix in English).

h4. External Links
* "Spider Mobile used as inspiration":[https://sonic.fandom.com/wiki/Spider_Mobile]
* "Original Post by Alpha Gamboa":[https://twitter.com/blackbookalpha/status/901971073096335360]

title: star_conflict
body:
Star Conflict is a free-to-play dynamic massively multiplayer online space action game. The gaming platform Steam describes it as an "action-packed, massively multiplayer space simulation game". The core of the game is PvP spaceships battles, PvE (Co-Op) missions and an open world. The game uses a free-to-play business model.

Star Conflict has been developed by the Russian company Targem Games (StarGem department) and published by Gaijin Entertainment. The game started on February 1, 2012 and reached open beta test on July 24, 2012. It has been available on Steam since February 27, 2013. The release took place on September 4, 2014 (Version 1.0).

http://star-conflict.com/en/

h4. Spaceships

There are 4 basic [[spacecraft|ship]] classes: [[interseptor_(star_conflict)|interceptors]], [[fighter_(star_conflict)|fighters]], [[frigate]]s and [[destroyer]]s. They are fundamentally different in external view, size, control, speed, etc. Each class has a variety of different modules available, weapons and features, designed for certain tasks. These variations determine the role of the ship on the battlefield.

title: counter_watch_(counter:side)
body:
A device in the setting of the game [[Counter:Side]], worn by humans who have become [i]Counters[/i].

It resembles an ordinary watch, but Counter watches function differently. The watch behaves more like the "Doomsday Clock":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doomsday_Clock].
If the time "runs out", the Counter wearing the watch turns into a [i]Shadow[/i], the Counter-equivalent of a Corrupted Object (abbreviated as C.O. in-game).

To keep the watch from ticking down and raise the timer up, the counter must feed the device with a special rare element dubbed [i]Eternium[/i].

title: scp-166
body:
Subject of the [[SCP Foundation]]. Codenamed [b]Teenage Succubus[/b], she is a normal teenage girl who goes nude due to her very fragile skin. As her name suggests, she has an unusual power to cause any nearby male who looks at her to want to have sex with her, to the point of obsession, which she is unable to control. These incidents cause distress for her as she is a Catholic nun who leads a chaste life. As a result, she lives in a secluded place protected by an all female SCP staff.

[spoilers]Strongly implied, if not flat-out stated in some places, to be [[Alto Clef]]'s daughter.[/spoilers]

Following revision in 2020, she is now codenamed [b]Just a Teenage Gaea[/b].  She is now a young woman with the antlers, hooves, and tail of a reindeer.  She has the paranormal ability to revert any artificially-created material or structure within 15 meters to an unrefined 'natural' state; the more advanced the material or device the faster it degrades.  Simultaneously, she causes plant life to grow within the same radius, even without any soil or seeds.  She is unable to control these abilities, so has to wear basic organic cotton clothes and live in a specially made containment chamber.  She retains her history as a devout catholic nun.

title: ko~n
body:
An onomatopoeic fox noise, probably a growl.

It's somewhat common for fox characters to say something to this effect on occasion, and the word "konkon" (コンコン) is even a diminutive word for foxes, but perhaps no one uses it more iconically than [[touhou|Touhou Project's]] [[Kudamaki Tsukasa]], for whom it can be considered a catchphrase. This stems from the fact that one of her in-game portraits displays her saying こーん right before her battle, notably written in Hiragana rather than Katakana, the alphabet typically reserved for onomatopoeia. Many fan works show her saying this, and Akatsuki Records even made a music video based entirely around Tsukasa making ko~n puns named ""Ko~nsultant!":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RypOHapqCeQ]."

title: hms_nelson
body: A British WW2 [[battleship]] armed with 9 16" guns in three triple turrets and capable of making 23 knots. The nameship of the first class of treaty battleships, Nelson can be best summed up as a cut-down [[G3 battlecruiser]]; maintaining comparable firepower to G3s but being 8 knots slower, slightly less well armored, and good 12 000 tons lighter when at full displacement, thanks to being designed within the limits imposed on new capital ships by the Washington Naval Treaty. HMS Nelson was laid down 28th of December 1922, launched 3rd of September 1925, commissioned 15th of August 1927, and ultimately scrapped in Inverkeithing, Scotland, in 1949.

title: backscratcher
body:
A backscratcher (also known as a scratch-back or a back scratcher) is a tool used for relieving an itch in an area that cannot easily be reached just by one's own hands, typically the back.

They are generally long, slender, and rod-shaped, with a knob on one end for holding and a rake-like device, sometimes in the form of a human hand, on the other end to perform the actual scratching.  Some variants feature massage rollers or a massage ball on the end opposite from the rake.

[[Penthesilea (fate)|]] in her Amazones CEO outfit from [[Fate/Grand Order]]. It's not much different than her Second Ascension attire, except she gains a pair of glasses and a black necktie. In the Servant Universe, a dimension completely separate to FGO's, Penthesilea works as the CEO for the intergalactic delivery company Amazones, an obvious parody of [[Amazon (company)|]] due to her being the queen of the Amazons. It's mostly her demeanor that changes rather than her attire, acting more like a professional businesswoman (although she still goes berserk whenever [[Achilles (fate)|]] is mentioned).

The additional glasses and necktie are part of a separate character skin for Penthesilea in-game, which changes some of her voice lines.
